{"title_page": "List of New York Red Bulls records and statistics", "text_new": "Records and statistics in relation to the American [[football (soccer)|soccer]] club '''[[New York Red Bulls|MetroStars/New York Red Bulls]]'''. They were founded in 1995 as the New York/New Jersey MetroStars and played their first competitive match in the inaugural [[1996 Major League Soccer season]]. In 2006 the club was renamed to the New York Red Bulls. \n\n==Honors==\n''As of 2019 season''<ref>https://us.soccerway.com/teams/united-states/new-york-red-bulls/6571/trophies/</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=MLS History |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331062551/https://www.mlssoccer.com/league/history |website=Major League Soccer |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*'''[[MLS Cup]]'''\n**''Runners Up'': [[MLS Cup 2008|2008]]\n*'''[[Supporters' Shield]]'''\n**'''Winners''' (3): [[2013 Major League Soccer season|2013]], [[2015 Major League Soccer season|2015]], [[2018 Major League Soccer season|2018]]\n*'''[[Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup]]'''\n**''Runners-up'' (2): [[2003 Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup|2003]],  [[2017 Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup|2017]]\n*'''[[Eastern Conference (MLS)|Eastern Conference]]'''\n**''Runners Up'' (Playoffs) (4): [[2000 Major League Soccer season|2000]], [[2014 Major League Soccer season|2014]], [[2015 Major League Soccer season|2015]], [[2018 Major League Soccer season|2018]]\n**'''Winners (Regular Season)''' (6): [[2000 Major League Soccer season|2000]], [[2010 Major League Soccer season|2010]], [[2013 Major League Soccer season|2013]], [[2015 Major League Soccer season|2015]], [[2016 Major League Soccer season|2016]], [[2018 Major League Soccer season|2018]]\n**''Runners Up'' (Regular Season): [[2001 Major League Soccer season|2001]]\n*'''[[Western Conference (MLS)|Western Conference]]'''\n**'''Winners (Playoff)''': 2008\n*'''Friendly Trophies'''\n**'''MLS Preseason Tournament''': 2001<ref>{{cite web |title=MetroStars Win 2001 MLS Preseason Tournament! |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010424204041/http://www.metrostars.com/preseason2001/preseason_03242001.htm |website=metrostars.com |accessdate=9 March 2020 |date=24 April 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Metros top San Jose, win spring training tournament - MetroStars / Red Bull New York - Major League Soccer |url=http://www.metrofanatic.com/story.jsp?ID=39 |website=www.metrofanatic.com |accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Obscure Metro Files: 2001 Spring Training Tournament - MetroStars / Red Bull New York - Major League Soccer |url=http://www.metrofanatic.com/story.jsp?ID=4843 |website=www.metrofanatic.com |accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n**'''[[Atlantic Cup (United States)|Atlantic Cup]]''' (8): 2003, 2010, 2011, 2013, 2015, 2017, 2018, 2019\n**'''[[La Manga Cup]]''': 2004 <!-- The Red Bulls did NOT \"win\" a La Manga Cup in 2010. The team's visit to La Manga and participation were not part of the tournament that year, of which there was only one. See [http://www.bigapplesoccer.com/teams/redbulls2.php?article_id=22103] for the story. -->\n**'''[[Walt Disney World Pro Soccer Classic]]''': [[2010 Walt Disney World Pro Soccer Classic|2010]]\n**'''[[Emirates Cup]]''': [[2011 Emirates Cup|2011]]\n\n==Records==\n''As of March 7, 2020''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorkredbulls.com/history/team#rbny09|title=New York Red Bulls History - Team|work=NewYorkRedBulls.com}}</ref>\n[[File:Mike Petke14.jpg|right|thumb|Former defender and manager, [[Mike Petke]] lead the club to its first major piece of silverware in 2013.]]\n===Team===\n*Victory: '''7\u20130''' v [[New York City FC]], May 21, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/new-york-city-vs-ny-red-bulls/353502|title=New York City 0-7 New York Red Bulls: Patrick Vieira's side crash to humiliating loss|work=SkySports.com}}</ref> \n* Draw with most goals: '''5\u20135''' v [[San Jose Earthquakes]], May 8, 2004<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/05/09/sports/metrostars-score-5-times-for-tie.html|title=MetroStars Score 5 Times for Tie|work=NYTimes.com}}</ref> \n* Defeat: '''0\u20136''' v [[Kansas City Wizards]], June 20, 1999<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com|title=MetroStars 6\u20130 vs. Kansas City Wizards|work=NYDailyNews.com}}</ref> \n* Most points in a season (3 pts per win): '''71''' ([[2018 Major League Soccer season|2018]], ''34 games'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2018/10/28/new-york-red-bulls-set-mls-points-record-win-3rd-supporters-shield|title=New York Red Bulls set MLS points record, win 3rd Supporters' Shield|work=MLSSoccer.com}}</ref> \n* Most victories in a season: '''22''' ([[2018 Major League Soccer season|2018]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2018/10/28/new-york-red-bulls-set-mls-points-record-win-3rd-supporters-shield|title=New York Red Bulls set MLS wins record, win 3rd Supporters' Shield|work=MLSSoccer.com}}</ref> \n* Fewest victories in a season: '''5''' ([[2009 Major League Soccer season|2009]])\n* Most goals scored in MLS season (team): '''64''' ([[2000 Major League Soccer season|2000]])\n\n===Individual===\n[[File:Bradley Wright Phillips nyrb.jpg|right|thumb|[[Bradley Wright-Phillips]] became the all-time leading scorer on July 31, 2016]]\n* Fastest goal scored: '''7 seconds''' [[Mike Grella]] ([[2015 Major League Soccer season|2015]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2015/10/18/mike-grella-scores-fastest-goal-mls-history-new-york-red-bulls-versus-philadelphia|title=Mike Grella scores fastest goal in MLS history for New York Red Bulls vs. Philadelphia Union|work=MLSSoccer.com}}</ref> \n* Most goals scored in MLS game (player): '''5''' [[Clint Mathis]] v [[Dallas Burn]], August 25, 2000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2000/aug/27/sports/sp-11246|title=MetroStars' Mathis Sets Record With Five-Goal Game|work=NYTimes.com}}</ref> \n* Most goals scored in MLS season (player): '''27''' [[Bradley Wright-Phillips]] ([[2014 Major League Soccer season|2014]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2014/10/27/bradley-wright-phillips-ties-mls-all-time-single-season-scoring-record|title=Bradley Wright-Phillips ties MLS all-time single season scoring record|work=NewYorkRedBulls.com}}</ref> \n* Most hat-tricks (Total): '''5''' [[Bradley Wright-Phillips]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2018/09/16/bradley-wright-phillips-notches-hat-trick-lead-red-bulls-point|title=Bradley Wright-Phillips Notches Hat Trick to Lead Red Bulls to a Point|work=NewYorkRedBulls.com}}</ref> \n* Most appearances (Total): '''281''' [[Luis Robles]]\n* Most appearances (MLS): '''239''' [[Luis Robles]]\n* Most appearances (Playoffs): '''23''' [[Luis Robles]]\n* Most appearances (Open Cup): '''14''' [[John Wolyniec]]\n* Most appearances (Continental): '''15''' [[Sean Davis (soccer)|Sean Davis]], [[Luis Robles]], [[Aaron Long (soccer)|Aaron Long]]\n* Most goals scored (Total): '''126''' [[Bradley Wright-Phillips]]\n* Most goals scored (MLS): '''108''' [[Bradley Wright-Phillips]]\n* Most goals scored (Playoffs): '''9''' [[Bradley Wright-Phillips]]\n* Most goals scored (Open Cup): '''7''' [[John Wolyniec]]\n* Most goals scored (Continental): '''4''' [[Bradley Wright-Phillips]], [[Daniel Royer]]\n\n===Managerial===\n* Most games managed (Total): '''151''' [[Jesse Marsch]]\n* Most victories (Total): '''76''' [[Jesse Marsch]]\n* Most losses (Total): '''46''' [[Octavio Zambrano]]\n\n==Player records==\n=== All-time top 10 appearances ===\n<!-- This is a list of all time appearance leaders in all competitive matches -->\n''As of March 7, 2020 (All competitive matches):'' <ref>http://metrofanatic.com/team/records.jsp?ALL=1&TYPE=0</ref> \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!width=30|Place\n!width=150|Name\n!width=125|Period\n!width=75|{{nobreak|MLS}}\n!width=75|{{nobreak|Playoffs}}\n!width=75|{{nobreak|Open Cup}}\n!width=75|{{nobreak|Continental}}\n!width=75|'''To