b record fee of $10million in 2008.\n}}\nAs per [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] rules and regulations; some transfer fees have been undisclosed and are not included in the tables below.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pressbox.mlssoccer.com/content/roster-rules-and-regulations|title=Rules and Regulations|work=MLSSoccer.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Highest transfer fees paid ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! !!Player!!From!!Fee!!Date!!Ref\n|-\n|1.||{{flagicon|PAR}} [[Alejandro Romero Gamarra|Kaku]]||{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n|Hurac\u00e1n]]||$6.25&nbsp;million|| February 2018 \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/new-york-red-bulls/story/3385696/red-bulls-finally-sign-kaku-gamarra-as-young-designated-player|title=Red Bulls finally sign 'Kaku' Gamarra as young designated player|work=ESPNFC.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|2.||{{flagicon|DEN}} [[Mathias J\u00f8rgensen (footballer, born 2000)|Mathias J\u00f8rgensen]]||{{flagicon|DEN}} [[Odense Boldklub]]||$2.5&nbsp;million|| February 2019\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prosoccerusa.com/mls/new-york-red-bulls/new-york-red-bulls-sign-danish-forward-mathias-jorgensen/|title=New York Red Bulls sign Danish forward Mathias J\u00f8rgensen|work=ProSoccerUSA.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|3.||{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Gonzalo Ver\u00f3n]]||{{flagicon|ARG}} [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]]||$2.2&nbsp;million|| August 2015\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2015/08/04/red-bulls-add-argentine-attacker-for-2-2-million/|title=Red Bulls add Argentine attacker for $2.2 million|work=NYPost.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|4.||{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Tim Cahill]]||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]||$1.55&nbsp;million|| July 2012 \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nypost.com:80/p/blogs/soccerblog/reports_red_bulls_acquire_everton_W1n6nq72FUT2QRYXqzM67L |title=Red Bulls acquire Cahill from Everton |work=Web.Archive.org |url-status=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120726031838/http://www.nypost.com/p/blogs/soccerblog/reports_red_bulls_acquire_everton_W1n6nq72FUT2QRYXqzM67L |archivedate=July 26, 2012 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Highest transfer fees received ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! !!Player!!To!!Fee!!Date!!Ref\n|-\n|1.||{{flagicon|USA}} [[Jozy Altidore]]||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Villarreal CF]]||$10&nbsp;million||June 2008\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/more-sports/red-bulls-jozy-altidore-headed-spain-villarreal-oks-transfer-article-1.291741|title=Red Bulls' Jozy Altidore headed for Spain after Villarreal OKs transfer|work=NYDailyNews.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|2.||{{flagicon|USA}} [[Matt Miazga]]||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]||$5&nbsp;million||January 2016 \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/new-york-red-bulls/story/2795020/matt-miazga-set-to-join-chelsea-of-the-premier-league|title=Source: Matt Miazga set to join Chelsea from New York Red Bulls|work=ESPNFC.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|3.||{{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Howard]]||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]||$4&nbsp;million||July 2003 \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/m/man_utd/3061333.stm|title=Howard joins Man Utd|work=News.BBC.co.uk}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|4.||{{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Ream]]||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]||$3&nbsp;million||January 2012 \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2012/01/26/new-york-mls-agree-transfer-fee-bolton-wanderers-fc-defender-tim-ream|title=New York, MLS Agree to Transfer Fee with Bolton Wanderers FC for Defender Tim Ream|work=NewYorkRedBulls.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Tyler Adams]]||{{flagicon|GER}} [[RB Leipzig]]||$3&nbsp;million||January 2019 \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/sources-tyler-adams-transfer-to-rb-leipzig-checks-in-at-3/q13tiqdvkqki1rkr3ay5ylmbd|title=Adams transfer to RB Leipzig checks in at $3 million with large sell-on clause|work=Goal.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|5.||{{flagicon|JAM}} [[Kemar Lawrence]]||{{flagicon|BEL}} [[R.S.C. Anderlec